-- Eskom Holdings Says South Africa Should Consider Importing Gas for Power
-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 2010-12-03T07:35:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-03/eskom-holdings-says-south-africa-should-consider-importing-gas-for-power.html
Eskom Holdings Ltd., South Africa’s
state-owned electricity utility, said the country should
consider importing gas for power.  Eskom’s senior general manager for regulatory affairs,
Mohamed Adam, made the comments in a speech in Johannesburg
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
